 if you need a small quantity of parts for your own instruments we suggest you contact a local music repair shop  lists of repair shops and other information for the public can be found at wwwnapbirtorg kmp is no longer a tool company we are now focused only on our core business which is supplying repair shops and manufacturers with the highest quality pads cork synthetic pads synthetic valve felts new materials for key corks and silencers glues solder and similar products   may  new step bevel synthetic pad we now make omnipads in two styles the classic taper radius style and a new step bevel style taper radius pads are labeled omnipad tr and step bevel pads are omnipad sb the new step bevel pads have the step bevel machined into the hard plastic backer which fully supports the foam layer and the proportions and shape are similar to our  clarinet pads we will have more technical information available soon but you can call us now to ask about all the synthetic pad options dont forget the non beveled ez pads are made from the same cushion and sealing layer foams and are an equally valid pad at a much lower price so long as your key cup is large enough for a non beveled pad to cover the tonehole      price list january st           website last updated may   pad prices have increased an average of  percent from the prices shown in our  price list     pads traditional and synthetic choose type clarinet flute saxophone pads piccolo pads oboe and bassoon omnipads ez pads sax pad resonators susfl straubinger copy cork pads bladder for pads cork and various sheet materials choose type natural sheet cork synthetic cork  natural wool felt synthetic felt gummi kork super tough brown foam teflon tech info about cork material comparison chart screws small plastic and metal parts choose type woodwind screws woodwind springs pilot pivot washers hinge rod washers flute pad washers flute pad stabilizers glue washers shrink tubing crack wire o rings bach tpt stop rod parts felt and 