e selected writings of karl kraus  ed frederick ungar includes poetry prose and aphorisms from die fackel as well as correspondences and excerpts from the last days of mankind in these great times a karl kraus reader  ed harry zohn contains translated excerpts from die fackel including poems with the original german text alongside and a drastically abridged translation of the last days of mankind antifreud karl kraus criticism of psychoanalysis and psychiatry  by thomas szasz contains szaszs translations of several of kraus articles and aphorisms on psychiatry and psychoanalysis half truths and oneandahalf truths selected aphorisms  translated by hary zohn chicago isbn  dicta and contradicta tr jonathan mcvity  a collection of aphorisms the last days of mankind  a radio drama broadcast on bbc three paul scofield plays the voice of god adapted and directed by giles havergal the  episodes were broadcast from  to  december  an incomplete english translation by michael russell of the last days of mankind is available at httpwwwthelastdaysofmankindcom it consists of a shortened version of acts i ii and iii totaling around  percent of the original text complete versions of selected scenes are being added this is part of a project to translate a complete performable text with an apparatus of footnotes the condensed version of acts iv and v will appear later the full translation will be published in two parts in  prologue i ii iii and  iv v epilogue the allverse epilogue is now published as a separate text available from amazon as a book and on kindle also on this site is a complete working translation by cordelia von klot provided as a tool for students and an accessible version of the whole play the kraus project essays by karl kraus  translated by jonathan franzen with commentary and additional footnotes by paul reitter and daniel kehlmann in these great times and other writings  translated with notes by patrick healy ebook only from november editions collection of eleven essays aphorisms and the prologue and first act of the last days of mankind wwwabitofpitchcom is dedicated to publishing selected writings of karl kraus in english translation with new translations appearing in irregular intervals the last days of mankind  complete text translated by fred bridgham and edward timms yale university press the last days of mankind  alternate translation by patrick healy november editions referencesedit citationsedit  stefan zweig die welt von gestern erinnerungen eines europäers frankfurt am main fischer    nomination database wwwnobelprizeorg retrieved    quoted following sprüche und widersprüche sayings and gainsayings suhrkamp frankfurtm  p   a b c d e siegfried mattl  the ambivalence of modernism from the weimar republic to national socialism and red vienna modern intellectual history volume  issue  april  pp –  a b c sascha bru gunther martens  the invention of politics in the european avantgarde – pp –  carl r mueller introduction to frank wedekind four major plays vol  lyme nh smith and krauss   willett  n  die fackel no  december  p   edward timms karl kraus apocalyptic satirist culture and catastrophe in habsburg vienna     kraus  die fackel nr  warum die fackel nicht erscheint p  quotation gewalt kein objekt der polemik  kovacsics adan  seleción de artículos de «die fackel» p  quotation la obra que kraus escribió en  pero que no publicó en parte como él mismo señala porque no puede ser «la violencia objeto de polémica ni la locura objeto de sátira» en parte porque temía comprometer a sus amigos y seguidores en alemania y ponerlos en peligro  freschi marino  preface to the italian translation of the third walpurgis night pp xxi–xxii  quotation il progetto venne bloccato dalle remore avvertite da kraus preoccupato di coinvolgere amici e conoscenti citati nel libro e ostili a hitler che ancora vivevano nel terzo reich  httpwwwclivejamescomkarlkraus  edward timms karl kraus apocalyptic satirist the postwar crisis and the rise of